title: Black Heart and White Heart
creator: H. Rider Haggard
description: LibriVox recording of Black Heart and White Heart, by H. Rider Haggard. Read by Vira Denton. Black Heart and White Heart, is a story of the courtship, trials and final union of a pair of Zulu lovers in the time of King Cetywayo. (Introduction by H. Rider Haggard) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (71MB)
subject: LibriVox; audiobooks; Zulu; South Africa; love story; King Cetywayo; H. Rider Haggard; Black Heart; White Heart; Black Heart and White Heart; Philip Hadden; Nahoon; Nanea; Doom pool
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
This is a typical H Rider Haggard adventure set in Africa. The reader is a local and pronounces the names perfectly. Although she has an accent, she is perfect for this book. She takes her time to read so it makes it much easier to read if you have a problem understanding accents. 

I highly recommend this book and the reader.

Esther
